The paper also introduces a new type of combinatorial structure (selectors), which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the development of clustering algorithms, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of the SINR model, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.IT, and cs.SI.
